     Actually wait, let me look again... the job is set to "processing" in `dequeue()`. If the job fails and doesn't call `fail()`, it stays as "processing". But in `dequeue()`,[0m[2m it only picks jobs with `status == "pending"`, so a "processing" job won't be picked up again.
     
     But the issue is that `dequeue()` doesn't actually mark the job as being picked up atomically with the iteration - there's an `await asyncio.sleep(0.01)` which is a yield point[0m[2m. Between checking `job["status"] == "pending"` and setting `job["status"] = "processing"`, other coroutines could run.
     
